Room 745 in the Cicerone (and perhaps others) is like a sauna if the temperature is over 50.	Opening the French windows to the terrace was only an option when one was not in the room as every bus in the city seems to roar its way along Via Cicerone.	Compared to Finnish hotels Cicerone is rather 3 stars than 4, but still ok place to stay.	While the location of the Cicerone is excellent, in particular for those with a special interest in St Peter's and the Vatican, and while rooms are adequate, we (my wife, adult son and I) were disappointed by a number of things.